.\" SSG - Static Site Generator
.\" Man page for ssg(1)
.TH SSG 1 "2026-07-15" "1.8.7" "SSG Manual"
.SH NAME
ssg \- fast static site generator written in Go
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ssg
.I source template domain
.RI [ options ]
.br
.B ssg
.B \-\-config
.I file
.RI [ options ]
.br
.B ssg
.B \-\-mddb\-url\fR=\fIURL
.B \-\-mddb\-collection\fR=\fINAME
.I template domain
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B ssg
is a fast and flexible static site generator that converts Markdown content
with YAML frontmatter into static HTML websites. It supports multiple template
engines (Go, Pongo2/Jinja2, Mustache, Handlebars), WebP image conversion,
built-in HTTP server with live reload, and deployment packaging for
Cloudflare Pages.
.PP
SSG can read content from local Markdown files or from a remote MDDB
(Markdown Database) server via HTTP or gRPC.
.SH ARGUMENTS
.TP
.I source
Content source folder name (inside content-dir). Not required when using
MDDB content source.
.TP
.I template
Template name (inside templates-dir).
.TP
.I domain
Target domain for the generated site (e.g., example.com).
.SH OPTIONS
.SS Configuration
.TP
.BR \-\-config =\fIFILE
Load configuration from a YAML, TOML, or JSON file. If not specified,
auto-detects \fB.ssg.yaml\fR, \fB.ssg.toml\fR, or \fB.ssg.json\fR in the
current directory.
.SS Template Engine
.TP
.BR \-\-engine =\fIENGINE
Template engine to use:
.BR go
(default),
.BR pongo2 ", " mustache " or " handlebars .
Non-Go engines render the theme's own templates verbatim in that engine's syntax.
.TP
.BR \-\-online\-theme =\fIURL
Download theme from a URL. Supports GitHub, GitLab repositories, or direct
ZIP file URLs.
.SS MDDB Content Source
.TP
.BR \-\-mddb\-url =\fIURL
MDDB server URL. Enables MDDB mode. Use \fBhttp://localhost:11023\fR for
HTTP or \fBlocalhost:11024\fR for gRPC.
.TP
.BR \-\-mddb\-protocol =\fIPROTO
Connection protocol: \fBhttp\fR (default) or \fBgrpc\fR.
.TP
.BR \-\-mddb\-collection =\fINAME
Collection name for fetching pages and posts.
.TP
.BR \-\-mddb\-key =\fIKEY
API key for MDDB authentication (optional).
.TP
.BR \-\-mddb\-lang =\fILANG
Language filter for MDDB documents (e.g., \fBen_US\fR, \fBpl_PL\fR).
.TP
.BR \-\-mddb\-timeout =\fISEC
Request timeout in seconds (default: 30).
.TP
.BR \-\-mddb\-batch\-size =\fIN
Batch size for pagination when fetching documents (default: 1000).
.TP
.B \-\-mddb\-watch
Watch MDDB for content changes and rebuild automatically.
.TP
.BR \-\-mddb\-watch\-interval =\fISEC
Polling interval for MDDB watch mode in seconds (default: 30).
.SS Server & Development
.TP
.B \-\-http
Start the built-in HTTP server after generating the site.
.TP
.BR \-\-host =\fIADDR
Dev server bind address (default: \fB127.0.0.1\fR). Use \fB0.0.0.0\fR to expose
the server on all network interfaces.
.TP
.BR \-\-port =\fIPORT
HTTP server port (default: 8888).
.TP
.B \-\-watch
Watch content and template directories for file changes and rebuild
automatically.
.TP
.B \-\-clean
Remove the output directory before building.
.SS Public Server Hardening (TLS/HTTP2/HTTP3)
All options below are opt-in. Enabling TLS negotiates HTTP/2 automatically (ALPN).
Security headers and cache-control are applied by the server automatically.
.TP
.BR \-\-tls\-cert =\fIFILE
PEM certificate for the built-in server. Combined with \fB\-\-tls\-key\fR this
serves HTTPS and enables HTTP/2.
.TP
.BR \-\-tls\-key =\fIFILE
PEM private key paired with \fB\-\-tls\-cert\fR.
.TP
.B \-\-tls\-auto
Obtain certificates automatically from Let's Encrypt (\fBautocert\fR). Requires
\fB\-\-tls\-domain\fR and binding port 443.
.TP
.BR \-\-tls\-domain =\fIHOST
Domain(s) authorized for automatic certificates (comma-separated).
.TP
.B \-\-http3
Serve HTTP/3 (QUIC) alongside HTTP/2 and advertise it via \fBAlt\-Svc\fR. Requires TLS.
.TP
.B \-\-gzip
gzip-compress responses when the client sends \fBAccept\-Encoding: gzip\fR.
.TP
.BR \-\-max\-conns =\fIN
Cap the number of simultaneous connections (\fB0\fR = unlimited).
.TP
.BR \-\-mem\-limit =\fISIZE
Runtime GC soft memory target, e.g. \fB512MiB\fR, \fB1GiB\fR.
.SS Output Control
.TP
.B \-\-sitemap\-off
Disable sitemap.xml generation.
.PP
Pages and posts are automatically excluded from sitemap.xml when any of the
following frontmatter conditions are met:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
\fBrobots\fR contains \fBnoindex\fR (e.g. \fBrobots: "noindex, follow"\fR)
.IP \(bu 2
\fBlayout: "redirect"\fR
.IP \(bu 2
\fBsitemap: "no"\fR
.RE
.TP
.B \-\-robots\-off
Disable robots.txt generation.
.TP
.BR \-\-pretty\-html ", " \-\-pretty
Clean up generated HTML by removing all blank lines, without aggressive
minification.
.TP
.B \-\-relative\-links
Convert absolute URLs containing the site domain to relative links.
Supports href, src, action attributes and url() in inline styles.
.TP
.BR \-\-post\-url\-format =\fIFMT
Post URL format. Options:
.RS
.TP
.B date
Date-based URLs: \fB/YYYY/MM/DD/slug/\fR (default).
.TP
.B slug
SEO-friendly slug-only URLs: \fB/slug/\fR.
.RE
.TP
.BR \-\-page\-format =\fIFMT
Page output format. Controls how HTML files are generated. Options:
.RS
.TP
.B directory
Each page generates \fBslug/index.html\fR (default). URLs end with
trailing slash: \fB/slug/\fR.
.TP
.B flat
Each page generates \fBslug.html\fR. URLs include the extension:
\fB/slug.html\fR.
.TP
.B both
Generates both \fBslug/index.html\fR and \fBslug.html\fR for maximum
compatibility. URLs use the directory form: \fB/slug/\fR.
.RE
.TP
.B \-\-minify\-all
Minify HTML, CSS, and JS output.
.TP
.B \-\-minify\-html
Minify only HTML output.
.TP
.B \-\-minify\-css
Minify only CSS output.
.TP
.B \-\-minify\-js
Minify only JS output.
.TP
.B \-\-sourcemap
Emit v3 source maps (\fB*.js.map\fR / \fB*.css.map\fR) for minified JS/CSS.
Minification becomes line-preserving so the mappings are exact and the original
source is embedded.
.TP
.B \-\-fingerprint
Content-hash CSS/JS to \fBname.<hash8>.ext\fR, write \fBassets-manifest.json\fR and
rewrite references in HTML and CSS (\fBurl()\fR/\fB@import\fR). Deterministic across
builds. Runs as the terminal asset step.
.TP
.B \-\-scss
Compile \fB*.scss\fR files in the output to \fB*.css\fR via the optional
\fBdart-sass\fR CLI before bundling/minify (partials \fB_*.scss\fR are only
resolved through @use/@import; all .scss sources are removed from the output).
A missing binary skips the step with a warning.
.TP
.BR \-\-sass\-binary =\fIPATH
Explicit dart-sass binary; default is \fBsass\fR resolved from PATH.
.TP
.BR \-\-paginate =\fIN
Posts per index page; adds \fB/page/N/\fR pages and a \fB.Pager\fR context. 0 disables
pagination (default).
.TP
.B \-\-lastmod\-from\-git
Derive sitemap \fB<lastmod>\fR from each source file's last git commit (fallback:
\fBmodified\fR/\fBdate\fR).
.TP
.BR \-\-permalink\-post =\fIPAT
Post URL pattern with tokens \fB:year :month :day :slug :category\fR
(e.g. \fB/:year/:month/:slug/\fR).
.TP
.BR \-\-permalink\-page =\fIPAT
Page URL pattern (same tokens).
.SS Authoring
.TP
.B \-\-math
Opt-in math: detect \fB$$...$$\fR / \fB```math\fR blocks and inject KaTeX only on
pages that use it.
.TP
.B \-\-sanitize\-html
Sanitize raw HTML embedded in markdown through the bluemonday UGC policy
(strips \fB<script>\fR and other unsafe markup).
.TP
.BR \-\-timezone =\fIZONE
Render content dates (permalink \fB:year/:month/:day\fR tokens and the
\fBDate\fR/\fBModified\fR template context) in the given IANA zone
(e.g. \fBEurope/Warsaw\fR). Per-language overrides via
\fBlanguage_timezones:\fR in the config file. Empty = no conversion.
.TP
.B \-\-highlight
Syntax-highlight code blocks via Chroma.
.TP
.BR \-\-highlight\-style =\fINAME
Chroma style (default: \fBgithub\fR).
.TP
.B \-\-toc
Expose \fB.TOC\fR to templates; the \fB[toc]\fR marker in content always expands.
.TP
.BR \-\-toc\-depth =\fIN
Maximum heading level included in the TOC (default: 3).
.SS Feeds, SEO and Search
.TP
.B \-\-feed
Generate an Atom \fBfeed.xml\fR at the root and per category/tag.
.TP
.BR \-\-feed\-items =\fIN
Maximum items per feed (default: 20).
.TP
.BR \-\-check\-links "[=" \fIstrict ]
Validate internal links against the output; \fBstrict\fR fails the build on a dead link.
.TP
.B \-\-search\-index
Emit \fBsearch-index.json\fR for client-side search.
.TP
.BR \-\-outputs =\fILIST
Per-page output formats, e.g. \fBhtml,json\fR (json writes index.json).
.TP
.B \-\-seo
Opt in to generator-level OpenGraph/Twitter/JSON-LD injection into pages that lack
their own tags (non-destructive). Off by default since v1.8.2; the legacy
\fB\-\-seo\-off\fR flag and \fBseo_off\fR config key force it off and print a
deprecation warning.
.SS Internationalization
.TP
.BR \-\-languages =\fILIST
Comma-separated languages (e.g. \fBpl,en\fR); non-default languages are emitted under
\fB/<lang>/\fR with \fBhreflang\fR alternates.
.TP
.BR \-\-default\-language =\fILANG
The default language, which is not prefixed in URLs.
.SS Image Processing
.TP
.B \-\-webp
Convert images to WebP format. Requires \fBcwebp\fR to be installed.
.TP
.BR \-\-webp\-quality =\fIN
WebP compression quality, 1\-100 (default: 60).
.TP
.B \-\-webp\-keep\-original
Emit each \fB.webp\fR next to its original instead of replacing it. Safe for
themes with hardcoded \fB.png\fR/\fB.jpg\fR references (favicons, logos,
og:image). The default replaces originals (historical behaviour).
.TP
.B \-\-reconvert\-images
Force reconversion of images even if WebP versions already exist.
.TP
.BR \-\-image\-sizes =\fIA,B,C
Responsive widths in px (e.g. \fB480,960,1600\fR): emit WebP variants and
\fB<img srcset>\fR (no upscaling).
.TP
.BR \-\-image\-sizes\-attr =\fIVAL
Value of the generated \fBsizes\fR attribute (default: \fB100vw\fR).
.TP
.B \-\-images\-gc
After the build, delete image-cache entries the site no longer references.
.TP
.B \-\-images\-gc\-dry
Report what \fB\-\-images\-gc\fR would delete (file count and bytes) without
deleting anything.
.SS Deployment
.TP
.B \-\-zip
Create a ZIP archive of the output tree (Cloudflare Pages ready).
.TP
.B \-\-targz
Create a gzip-compressed tarball (\fB.tar.gz\fR) of the output tree.
.TP
.B \-\-tarxz
Create an xz-compressed tarball (\fB.tar.xz\fR) of the output tree.
.SS Native Publish
Deploy runs after the build (and after \fB\-\-webp\fR/\fB\-\-zip\fR). All secrets are
read from the environment, never the config file.
.TP
.BR \-\-deploy =\fIPROVIDER
Publish the output tree to \fIcloudflare\fR, \fIgithub-pages\fR, \fInetlify\fR,
\fIvercel\fR, \fIftp\fR or \fIsftp\fR.
.TP
.BR \-\-deploy\-project =\fINAME
Pages/site/project name (cloudflare, netlify, vercel).
.TP
.BR \-\-deploy\-branch =\fIBRANCH
Target branch for cloudflare / github-pages (default \fBgh-pages\fR).
.TP
.BR \-\-deploy\-target =\fIURL
An \fBftp://\fR/\fBsftp://\fR URL, or a git remote for github-pages.
.PP
Required environment per provider: \fBcloudflare\fR — CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN,
CLOUDFLARE_ACCOUNT_ID; \fBgithub-pages\fR — GITHUB_TOKEN (https) or an SSH key;
\fBnetlify\fR — NETLIFY_AUTH_TOKEN (+ NETLIFY_SITE_ID); \fBvercel\fR — VERCEL_TOKEN,
VERCEL_ORG_ID; \fBftp\fR — FTP_USERNAME, FTP_PASSWORD; \fBsftp\fR — SSH_USERNAME,
SSH_PASSWORD or SSH_KEY_FILE (the host must be present in known_hosts).
.SS Paths
.TP
.BR \-\-content\-dir =\fIPATH
Content directory (default: \fBcontent\fR).
.TP
.BR \-\-templates\-dir =\fIPATH
Templates directory (default: \fBtemplates\fR).
.TP
.BR \-\-output\-dir =\fIPATH
Output directory (default: \fBoutput\fR).
.TP
.BR \-\-static\-dir =\fIPATH
Static passthrough directory (default: \fBstatic\fR). Every file and
subdirectory it contains is copied verbatim into the output directory during
generation. A missing directory is a no-op.
.TP
.BR \-\-data\-dir =\fIPATH
Data files directory (default: \fBdata\fR). \fB*.yaml\fR/\fB*.json\fR files are loaded
into the \fB.Data.*\fR template namespace, nested by subdirectory.
.SS Other
.TP
.BR \-\-quiet ", " \-q
Suppress all output; only exit codes indicate success or failure.
.TP
.BR \-\-version ", " \-v
Print the version and exit.
.TP
.BR \-\-help ", " \-h
Print usage information and exit.
.SH CONFIGURATION FILE
SSG supports configuration via YAML, TOML, or JSON files. The config file
is specified with \fB\-\-config\fR or auto-detected as \fB.ssg.yaml\fR,
\fB.ssg.toml\fR, or \fB.ssg.json\fR.
.PP
Example \fB.ssg.yaml\fR:
.PP
.RS
.nf
source: "my-content"
template: "simple"
domain: "example.com"
webp: true
webp_quality: 80
pretty_html: true
post_url_format: "slug"
engine: "go"

shortcode_brackets: true
shortcodes:
  - name: "promo"
    template: "shortcodes/banner.html"
    title: "Special Offer"
    text: "Get 50% off!"
    url: "https://example.com"

variables:
  gtm: "GTM-XXXXXXX"
  analytics_id: "$GA_ID"
  api:
    endpoint: "https://api.example.com"

pages_path: "docs"
posts_path: "articles"
rewrite_md_links: true
preserve_slug_case: false

mddb:
  enabled: true
  url: "http://localhost:11023"
  collection: "blog"
  protocol: "http"
  lang: "en_US"
  watch: true
  watch_interval: 30
.fi
.RE
.SH CONTENT PATHS
By default SSG reads static pages from the \fBpages/\fR subdirectory and blog
posts from the \fBposts/\fR subdirectory inside the content source. Both can be
overridden:
.TP
.B pages_path
Subdirectory name for static pages (default: \fBpages\fR).
Example: \fBpages_path: "docs"\fR reads from \fBcontent/{source}/docs/\fR.
.TP
.B posts_path
Subdirectory name for blog posts (default: \fBposts\fR).
Example: \fBposts_path: "articles"\fR reads from \fBcontent/{source}/articles/\fR.
.SH SLUG HANDLING
Slugs are read from the \fBslug:\fR field in frontmatter. When no slug is set,
it is automatically derived from the source filename (without the \fB.md\fR
extension).
.PP
By default slugs are lowercased (\fBAPI.md\fR → \fB/api/\fR). Set
\fBpreserve_slug_case: true\fR to keep the original casing (\fBAPI.md\fR →
\fB/API/\fR).
.SH MD LINK REWRITING
When \fBrewrite_md_links: true\fR is set, relative \fB.md\fR hrefs in content
are rewritten to their final output URLs during the build.
.PP
For example \fBhref="AUTHENTICATION.md"\fR becomes
\fBhref="/authentication/"\fR (or whatever the slug resolves to).
.PP
Relative path prefixes (\fB./\fR, \fB../dir/\fR) are stripped — only the base
filename is matched. Unknown \fB.md\fR links are left untouched. The feature is
opt-in to avoid breaking sites that intentionally serve raw \fB.md\fR files.
.SH EXTERNAL SOURCES
The config-only \fBexternal_sources\fR block feeds templates from local files
(YAML/JSON/TOML/CSV/XML), remote HTTP APIs (hardened client, shared disk
cache with TTL/stale-if-error/offline), read-only SQL queries
(MySQL/MariaDB/PostgreSQL/SQLite) and CMS imports (WordPress, Drupal,
Movable Type; \fBmode: content\fR merges them into the site). Data is exposed
as \fB{{.ExternalData.<name>}}\fR and via \fBgetExternal\fR; secrets come only
from environment variables. See \fBdocs/EXTERNAL_SOURCES.md\fR.
.TP
.B \-\-offline
Serve external HTTP sources from the disk cache only (no network).
.TP
.B \-\-refresh\-external\-sources
Ignore fresh cache entries and re-fetch external sources.
.TP
.B \-\-clear\-external\-cache
Wipe the external-source disk cache before the build.
.TP
.BR \-\-external\-source =\fINAME
Narrow \fB\-\-refresh\-external\-sources\fR to one source.
.SH SERVER ACCESS CONTROL
Config-only options harden the built-in server: \fBserver_auth\fR (\fBbasic\fR
with \fBserver_users\fR entries of the form \fBlogin:$PASS_ENV\fR, or
\fBjwt\fR with an HS256 \fBjwt_secret\fR from the environment),
\fBip_allowlist\fR/\fBip_blocklist\fR (IPs or CIDRs), and a per-IP token-bucket
rate limiter (\fBrate_limit\fR requests/second, \fBrate_burst\fR bucket size).
The chain runs blocklist, allowlist, rate limiter, then auth. SSO and LDAP are
deliberately not implemented.
.SH TAXONOMIES
\fBcategory\fR, \fBtag\fR and \fBseries\fR are built in; additional dynamic
taxonomies are declared in the config file under the \fBtaxonomies\fR key
(config-only, no CLI flag). Each taxonomy gets a term index (e.g.
\fB/technology/\fR) and per-term archives (\fB/technology/go/\fR) with
template fallback chains, optional per-term Atom feeds, sitemap entries and
term metadata from \fBdata/taxonomies/<name>.yaml\fR. Frontmatter sources are
merged by priority: the \fBtaxonomies:\fR map, then the configured field, then
the legacy fields. See \fBdocs/TAXONOMIES.md\fR for the full reference.
.SH CONFIG VARIABLES
Define custom variables in \fB.ssg.yaml\fR under the \fBvariables\fR key. They are
available in every template context as \fB{{.Vars.key}}\fR and exported as
environment variables with the \fBSSG_\fR prefix at build time.
.PP
Nested maps are supported: \fB{{.Vars.api.endpoint}}\fR is exported as
\fBSSG_API_ENDPOINT\fR.
.PP
Values starting with \fB$\fR are resolved from the current OS environment
(e.g. \fB"$GTM_CODE"\fR reads the \fBGTM_CODE\fR env var). If the env var is not
set the literal value is kept unchanged.
.PP
Example:
.RS
.nf
variables:
  gtm: "GTM-XXXXXXX"        # {{.Vars.gtm}}, exported as SSG_GTM
  analytics_id: "$GA_ID"    # resolved from $GA_ID at build time
  api:
    endpoint: "https://api.example.com"  # SSG_API_ENDPOINT
.fi
.RE
.SH TEMPLATE ENGINES
SSG supports rendering templates with four different template engines.
Select the engine with the
.B \-\-engine
flag or the
.B engine
configuration option.
.TP
.B go
Go's standard \fBhtml/template\fR package (default). Uses \fB{{ .Field }}\fR
syntax. Provides the full helper FuncMap and Go block inheritance.
.TP
.B pongo2
Jinja2/Django-like template syntax. Non-Go engines must contain templates authored in their respective syntax.
.TP
.B mustache
Logic-less templates using the Mustache syntax family.
.TP
.B handlebars
Handlebars blocks and helpers.
.SH TEMPLATE VARIABLES
All page/post fields are available at the template root level for direct access.
Custom metadata fields from MDDB frontmatter are also flattened to root level.
.PP
.B Standard fields:
.RS
.nf
{{ .Title }}        \- Page/post title
{{ .Slug }}         \- URL slug
{{ .Content }}      \- Rendered HTML content
{{ .Date }}         \- Publication date
{{ .Modified }}     \- Last modification date
{{ .Excerpt }}      \- Content excerpt
{{ .URL }}          \- Page URL path
{{ .CanonicalURL }} \- Full canonical URL
{{ .Description }}  \- SEO description
{{ .Keywords }}     \- SEO keywords
{{ .Tags }}         \- Tags array
{{ .WordCount }}    \- Word count of the content
{{ .ReadingTime }}  \- Estimated reading time in minutes
{{ .HasMath }}      \- True if the page contains math (with \fB\-\-math\fR)
{{ .Series }}       \- Series name (if any)
{{ .SeriesPrevURL }}   \- Previous-in-series URL/title
{{ .SeriesNextURL }}   \- Next-in-series URL/title
{{ .Pager }}        \- Pagination state on the index (Current/Total/PrevURL/NextURL)
{{ .Data }}         \- Data files namespace (\fB.Data.site.name\fR, ...)
{{ .Lang }}         \- Page language
{{ .Languages }}    \- Configured languages
{{ .Translations }} \- Language variants of this page (switcher)
{{ .Hreflang }}     \- Ready-to-use <link rel="alternate" hreflang> markup
.fi
.RE
.PP
.B Custom fields (from MDDB metadata):
.RS
.nf
{{ .dupa }}         \- Custom field "dupa"
{{ .defaultVideo }} \- Custom field "defaultVideo"
{{ .playlist }}     \- Custom field "playlist"
.fi
.RE
.PP
For backward compatibility, \fB{{ .Page.Title }}\fR and \fB{{ .Post.Title }}\fR
still work.
.SH CO-LOCATED ASSETS
Images and other media files placed alongside Markdown content files are
automatically copied to the corresponding output directory. This allows
you to reference images with simple relative paths in your Markdown.
.PP
For example, if you have:
.PP
.RS
.nf
content/my-site/pages/about.md
content/my-site/pages/about-photo.png
.fi
.RE
.PP
The \fBabout-photo.png\fR will be copied to \fBoutput/about/about-photo.png\fR,
and you can reference it in \fBabout.md\fR as:
.PP
.RS
.nf
![Photo](about-photo.png)
.fi
.RE
.PP
Supported asset types: PNG, JPG, JPEG, GIF, SVG, WebP, ICO, BMP, TIFF,
AVIF, MP4, WebM, OGG, MP3, WAV, PDF, ZIP.
.SH BUILT-IN THEMES
.TP
.B simple
Modern dark theme with glassmorphism effects, purple gradient accents, and
micro-animations.
.TP
.B krowy
Light green farm theme inspired by krowy.net, with natural colors and
organic design.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Successful execution.
.TP
.B 1
Error during generation, invalid configuration, or missing required
arguments.
.SH EXAMPLES
Generate a site with the simple template:
.PP
.RS
.nf
ssg my-site simple example.com
.fi
.RE
.PP
Start development server with live reload:
.PP
.RS
.nf
ssg my-site simple example.com --http --watch
.fi
.RE
.PP
Build with minification, WebP conversion and multiple archives:
.PP
.RS
.nf
ssg my-site krowy example.com --clean --minify-all --webp --zip --targz --tarxz
.fi
.RE
.PP
Serve publicly over HTTPS with HTTP/3, gzip and a connection cap:
.PP
.RS
.nf
ssg my-site simple example.com --http --port=443 \\
    --tls-cert=cert.pem --tls-key=key.pem --http3 --gzip --max-conns=1024
.fi
.RE
.PP
Serve publicly with automatic Let's Encrypt certificates:
.PP
.RS
.nf
ssg my-site simple example.com --http --port=443 \\
    --tls-auto --tls-domain=example.com --mem-limit=512MiB
.fi
.RE
.PP
Build and publish natively to Cloudflare Pages:
.PP
.RS
.nf
CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN=… CLOUDFLARE_ACCOUNT_ID=… \\
    ssg my-site krowy example.com --deploy=cloudflare --deploy-project=my-site
.fi
.RE
.PP
Publish over SFTP with key-based auth:
.PP
.RS
.nf
SSH_KEY_FILE=~/.ssh/id_ed25519 \\
    ssg my-site krowy example.com --deploy=sftp --deploy-target=sftp://deploy@example.com/var/www
.fi
.RE
.PP
Use Pongo2 template engine with an online theme:
.PP
.RS
.nf
ssg my-site mytheme example.com --engine=pongo2 \\
    --online-theme=https://github.com/user/hugo-theme
.fi
.RE
.PP
Use MDDB content source with gRPC:
.PP
.RS
.nf
ssg --mddb-url=localhost:11024 --mddb-protocol=grpc \\
    --mddb-collection=blog krowy example.com
.fi
.RE
.PP
Load all settings from config file:
.PP
.RS
.nf
ssg --config .ssg.yaml --http --watch
.fi
.RE
.SH FILES
.TP
.I .ssg.yaml
Default YAML configuration file (auto-detected).
.TP
.I .ssg.toml
Default TOML configuration file (auto-detected).
.TP
.I .ssg.json
Default JSON configuration file (auto-detected).
.TP
.I content/
Default content directory containing Markdown files.
.TP
.I templates/
Default templates directory containing theme files.
.TP
.I output/
Default output directory for generated HTML.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
SSG uses the following environment variables:
.TP
.B CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN ", " CLOUDFLARE_ACCOUNT_ID
Credentials for the Cloudflare Pages deployment provider.
.TP
.B GITHUB_TOKEN
Authentication token for the GitHub Pages deployment provider.
.TP
.B NETLIFY_AUTH_TOKEN ", " NETLIFY_SITE_ID
Credentials for the Netlify deployment provider.
.TP
.B VERCEL_TOKEN ", " VERCEL_ORG_ID
Credentials for the Vercel deployment provider.
.TP
.B FTP_USERNAME ", " FTP_PASSWORD
Credentials for the FTP deployment provider.
.TP
.B SSH_USERNAME ", " SSH_PASSWORD ", " SSH_KEY_FILE ", " SSH_KEY_PASSPHRASE ", " SSH_KNOWN_HOSTS
Credentials and settings for the SFTP deployment provider.
.TP
.B SSG_OUTPUT_DIR ", " SSG_PHASE ", " SSG_PAGE_PATH
Context variables supplied to custom build hooks during execution.
.PP
Additionally, any custom variables defined under the
.B variables
key in configuration are exported to build hooks with the
.B SSG_
prefix. Values starting with
.B $
in configuration are resolved from matching host environment variables at build time.
